{{> head}}
	<article class="future-of-tv">
	<header class="header">
		<div class="header__logo">
			<a class="header__logo-link" href="/">
				<img class="header__logo-img" src="/assets/svg/odd-networks.svg" alt="Odd Networks">
			</a>
		</div>
		<div class="header__page-break">
			<!-- This silliness is to avoid the spacing between inline-block elements -->
			<span class="header__page-break__block blue"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block purple"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block magenta"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block pink"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block red"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block orange"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block yellow"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block yellow-green"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block green"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block light-green"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block cyan"
			></span><span class="header__page-break__block light-blue"></span>
		</div>
	</header>
	<section class="constrained clearfix">
		<header class="future-of-tv__hero">
			<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h1 future-of-tv__block">
				<span class="highlight">Your brand is on the bleeding edge of a new era of television.</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="headline-font headline-font--h2 future-of-tv__hero-subheader">
				Technology needs to catch up.
			</p>
			<p class="future-of-tv__hero-img"><img src="/assets/img/old-tv.jpg"></p>
		</header>
		<div class="future-of-tv__hero-summary">
			<p class="headline-font headline-font--h3 future-of-tv__hero-odd-networks future-of-tv__block">
				<span class="highlight">Odd Networks</span> is a band of geeks holed up in a mostly secret
				hideout to build the <span class="highlight">television platform of the future.</span>
			</p>
			<p class="subheader future-of-tv__block">You'll be able to distribute your content anywhere,
			on any platform, and collect the data to prove it. Together we'll change TV forever.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="future-of-tv__hero-cta">
			<p><a class="cta-button" href="#foo">Request Early Access</a></p>
			<p class="summary">Not sure? Read on.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
	<div class="future-of-tv__page-break header__page-break">
		<!-- This silliness is to avoid the spacing between inline-block elements -->
		<span class="header__page-break__block blue"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block purple"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block magenta"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block pink"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block red"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block orange"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block yellow"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block yellow-green"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block green"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block light-green"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block cyan"
		></span><span class="header__page-break__block light-blue"></span>
	</div>
	<section class="constrained future-of-tv__benefits clearfix">
		<header>
			<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2">
				<span class="highlight">Awesome sh*t you'll be able to do:</span>
			</h1>
		</header>
		<section class="future-of-tv__benefit-sub-section--left">
			<section class="future-of-tv__benefit-container">
				<header>
					<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2">Your own branded apps.</h1>
				</header>
				<ul class="subheader">
					<li>Launch apps on Apple TV, Roku, FireTV, and more.</li>
					<li>Add mobile apps for Apple and Android devices.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section class="future-of-tv__benefit-container">
				<header>
					<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2">Know your audience like never before.</h1>
				</header>
				<ul class="subheader">
					<li>Collect and merge analytical data from your website and all your apps.</li>
					<li>Oh, and YouTube, Facebook and Twitter too.</li>
					<li>Use artificial intelligence for content programming.</li>
					<li>Run your own content programming. You know, so the bots don't take over.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</section>
		<section class="future-of-tv__benefit-sub-section--right">
			<section class="future-of-tv__benefit-container">
				<header>
					<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2">Own the World.</h1>
				</header>
				<ul class="subheader">
					<li>Selectively push content to YouTube, Facebook and Twitter.</li>
					<li>Be the next generation of TV.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section class="future-of-tv__benefit-container">
				<header>
					<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2">Make it rain.</h1>
				</header>
				<ul class="subheader">
					<li>Add a subscription service.</li>
					<li>Run advertising.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</section>
	</section>
	<section class="constrained clearfix">
		<section>
			<header>
				<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2">Still not sure?</h1>
				<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h3">How much?</h1>
			</header>
			<p class="subheader">Probably less then $100 a month.</p>
			<p class="headline-font headline-font--h3"><span class="highlight">No. Really. How much?</span></p>
			<p class="subheader">Really. Probably less then $100 a month.</p>
			<p><a class="cta-button" href="#foo">Request Early Access</a></p>
		</section>
		<section class="future-of-tv__faq">
			<header>
				<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h1">FAQ</h1>
			</header>
			<p class="headline-font headline-font--h3">Distribute to any platform? Really?</p>
			<p class="summary">
				Yeah. Really. Odd Networks has sample and template apps to cover most of the major platforms. But with the Software Development Kits you'll be able to launch an app on literally any device that will play video.
			</p>
			<p class="headline-font headline-font--h3">WTF is an API? An SDK?</p>
			<p class="summary">
				Geeks like us use acronyms to make it harder to understand than it has to be.
			</p>
			<p class="summary">Sorry.</p>
			<p class="summary">
			Application Programming Interfaces (APIs) and Software Development Kits (SDKs) allow developers to integrate with literally anything. Facebook? Yep. YouTube? Yes. Google Analytics? Sure. Twitter? Absolutely. IFTT, Hootsuite, Buffer, Zapier ... yes! Literally. Anything.
			</p>

			<p class="headline-font headline-font--h3">Can I make it so that people can actually buy products they see in my content? Can they choose which camera they are viewing at a live event? Can I launch an app on a Mars rover and beam back video of Matt Damon?
			</p>
			<p class="summary">
				Yes. The Odd Networks Software Development Kits and Application Programming Interfaces make it possible for developers to do just about anything you can imagine. Be careful. With great power comes great responsibility.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section>
			<header>
				<h1 class="headline-font headline-font--h2"><span class="highlight">More Questions?</span></h1>
			</header>
			<p><a class="cta-button" href="#foo">Request Early Access</a></p>
			<p class="subheader">You'll get our email address. Ask us anything.</p>
		</section>
	</section>
	</article>
</body>
</html>
